@node "install" "MuiMore Locale installation"

Copy the catalog of your language
(MUIMore_110_Locale/catalogs/your_language/Muimore.catalog) to
locale:catalogs/your_language/ or, if you prefer, create a
catalogs/your_language/ directory in the MUIMore directory, and copy the
catalog o your language inside of it.

@endnode

@node "intro" "Introduction"

Well... some times ago, I release MUIMore 1.10, a nice MUI based text viewer
with some interesting functions... lot of people sent me mail telling that the
program was great, and some of them also asked me the catalog blank files to
translate MUIMore in their languages. I gave them the .cd file and, after a
short period of time, they give me back the translated files. I promised them
that I would have released the catalogs very soon.... but I'm so lazy that
I never did it...until now :)

Here you'll find the catalogs of some languages, and also the deutsch
AmigaGuide files, kindly translated by these great @{"authors" link "aut" 0}.

Because of my lazyness, I also decide to insert into this archive the .cd file,
so that everybody will be able to translate the catalog in his own language,
without having to ask me the .cd file. BTW, if you do so, don't' forget (as me!)
to upload your work on Aminet, and please send @{"me" link "Autore" 0} a copy of the catalog.

@endnode

