@node "II" "MUIMore II ???"

Ok... as some of you probably know... I overwrote the main source file
of MUIMore (how stupid am I ??). I tried everything, but AFS phisically
deleted the source from my hard disk and, of course, I didn't make any
backup........:9

Last week (about 6 months after the source missing) I saw in my kitchen
a big piece of paper with a big writing on it: "Call the baker" and (I
couldn't believe my eyes, under the "baker" I saw something like
"search(item,mode)...". IT WAS A PIECE of MUIMore source ! Then I remembered
that long time ago, I printed a copy of the source to work on, and then I gave
it to my mother, to use as post-it because I dind't need it anymore.
Now I found about 75% of the source the I printed, which was MUIMore
version 1.05.

I had a look at the source (tring to ignore baker & other funny words :]] ) and
I noticed that MUIMore was coded very badly (it was my first AmigaE program..),
so it would have been quiet stupid coping this badly coded program back on
my Amiga.

But you don't have to worry: I'm thinking about a completly new version, written
from scratch, and I'll probably do it this summer. It will be MUIMore II ! :)
In this new version, the MUI listview will be substituded by the MCC Nlistview,
and some interesting feature will be made in this new version. The program will
also be fastest, because I won't do again some very stupid thing I found in the
old source...

The problem is that I don't know if I should make a new Amiga MUIMore II version or
if it would be better to make a pOS version (I'm pOS developer)... pOS looks great,
.... I really don't know what to do.. you'll discover it this summer ! (final version
should be ready before september...)

@endnode
